    "Tennessee State Graduate On USDA Feed Grain Committee Hilliard Currin 700acre cot ton cattle and grain farmer of Brownsville Tenn was named last week by Secretary Orville L Freeman to the U S De partment of Agricultures Ad visory Committee on Feed Grains and Wheat The committee meets at the call of the Secretary to advise him on major legislative propo sals and other matters related to feed grains and wheat Mr Currin a graduate of Tennessee A and I State Uni versity was reared on his par ents West Tennessee farm which he took over several years ago He is the first Negro to be appointed to the important Feed Grain and Wheat Commit tee Social Science Continued From Page One tute to students interested in taking the Civil Service and Graduate Record examinations as well as the Medical and Law School admission tests In conjunction with the well known forums of the Social Science Division two seminars have been offered by the Insti tute this fall An InterAmeri can Affairs seminar prepared students for the October 2 forum and another seminar on the United Nations with Dr Ralph Bunche on October 23 The success of the Social Sci"
